{ { Village among the Trees
This area can be divided into two.The western half contains one of the largest semi-deciduous woodlands in Southern England designated an area of Special Scientific Interest.The Eastern half contains the pretty village of West Tytherley(Tytherley is mentioned in the Domesday Book). This village was part of the Washington Singer Estate based on the Historic House of Norman Court(now Northaw School).It retains much of its original character with timber framed thatched cottages.Preservation is apparent for both woodland and village An estimate for the whole area is about 600 people but with trees,trees and more trees!
